# Supabase Connection Standard

## Always use session pooler — never direct host
postgresql://postgres.dpmuvynqixblxsilnlut:PASSWORD@aws-1-us-east-2.pooler.supabase.com:5432/postgres

- Host: `aws-1-us-east-2.pooler.supabase.com`
- Port: `5432` (session pooler — supports transactions + prepared statements)
- User: `postgres.dpmuvynqixblxsilnlut` (includes project ref)
- Never use `db.dpmuvynqixblxsilnlut.supabase.co` — IPv6 only, not reachable from Mac or Workers

## Never use transaction pooler port 6543 in scripts
Port 6543 is for Workers AI / Hyperdrive only. Local Python scripts use 5432.

## Hyperdrive binding in Worker
```js
const conn = env.HYPERDRIVE.connectionString; // use this, never hardcode
```
Hyperdrive ID: `08183bb9d2914e87ac8395d7e4ecff60`

## Password location
Stored in `.env.cloudflare` as `SUPABASE_DB_URL`. Never hardcode in committed files.
Scripts that need it: read from `os.getenv("SUPABASE_DB_URL")` with the session pooler URL as default.

## Embedding scripts
- Embed model: `ollama:mxbai-embed-large` (1024-dim, local)
- Always set `embed_model = "ollama:mxbai-embed-large"` on rows after embedding
- Always write vector back to Supabase `embedding` column AND push to Vectorize
- Vectorize index: `ai-search-inneranimalmedia-autorag`
- Filter tag pattern: `{"source": "memory"|"skill"|"tool"|"route"|"architecture"|"decision"}`
